            <scopecontent id="aspace_d5e5d04f3f3b8e4ca7f455f346941489">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>TAGS is comprised reports, memos, maps, studies, advertisements, newspaper clippings, correspondence, and cassette tapes related to a campaign against the Harrisonburg City Council's plans to build a municipal golf course in the Hillandale Park in Harrisonburg. The organization eventually formed the Citizens of Harrisonburg Advocating New Government for the Electorate (CHANGE) in 2000, who endorsed three candidates for city council -- Dorn Peterson, Carolyn Frank, and Joe Fitzgerald â all of whom were elected in May 2000.</p>
            </scopecontent>
